In addition to phytonutrients mainly presented in fruit and vegetables, polyphenols have recently been targeted due to their role in the prevention of several diseases as described (
 Fraga 
  et al., 2019
 ). Interestingly, polyphenols have attracted much attention in recent years since their dietary consumption has been associated with the prevention of some chronic and degenerative diseases that are significant causes of death and incapacity in developing countries (
 Santos-Buelga 
  et al., 2019
 ). In addition, due to the biological activities of polyphenols, particularly antimicrobial, antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, pro-apoptotic behavior, anti-proliferative, and hormonal control ability among polyphenols, countless plants have been considered and investigated because of the classification of new substances with nutraceutical possessions (
 Forni 
  et al., 2019
 ). Dietary polyphenols signify several bioactive substances broadly found in plant-based food which have the capabilities to prevent the beginning and development of several diseases, and to decrease and control their signs which become a central issue in food research (
 Del Bo 
  et al., 2019
 ; 
 Quero 
  et al., 2020
 ).
